<TITLE> Road accident kills 18 in Tangail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tangail, April 19 (bdnews24.com)  At least 18 people died and another 50 were injured after a speeding bus overturned in Kalihati, Tangail, Saturday, officials said. bdnews24.com correspondent KS Rahman Shafi reported from the scene that 16 passengers died instantly and and another two died of critical injuries in hospital. The bus was bound for Dhaka from Kurigram. The speeding bus overturned onto a rail line on the Dhaka-Tangail Jamuna Bridge highway around 6.00am killing five people instantly, said Tangail deputy commissioner Md Akhter Ali Sarker. 11 more bodies were found two hours later when the bus was pulled upright by a bulldozer. Two people died after being rushed to hospital. Forty-six of the injured were admitted to Tangail General Hospital and four others were given first aid on the spot. The accident suspended rail movement on the Dinajpur-Dhaka route for three hours. Of the dead only seven could be identified so far. They are: Abdus Sattar, 26, of Nalatari village in Kurigram; Nurul Islam of Char Berubari village; Musa, 28, of Sarderpara village; Razzak, 46, of Shalmara village; Rafiqul Islam, 25; Johurul Islam, 40; Monjur Alam, 25. bdnews24.com
